 How to Use External Databases in Neurodiagnoses
To enhance the accuracy of our diagnostic models, Neurodiagnoses integrates data from multiple biomedical and neurological research databases. If you are a researcher, follow these steps to access, prepare, and integrate data into the Neurodiagnoses framework.

1ï¸âƒ£ Register for Access
Each database requires a separate registration and access approval. Follow the official access guidelines for each platform.

2ï¸âƒ£ Download & Prepare Data
Once granted access, download datasets following the specific data usage terms. Ensure the files meet Neurodiagnoses' format requirements for integration.

Supported File Formats: .csv, .tsv, .nii (neuroimaging), .fasta (genetics)
Mandatory Fields for Integration: Subject ID, Diagnosis, Biomarkers, Genetic Data, Neuroimaging Metadata
3ï¸âƒ£ Upload Data to Neurodiagnoses
Option 1: Manually upload to EBRAINS Bucket â†’ [Collabs/neurodiagnoses/Bucket]
Option 2: Contribute via GitHub Repository â†’ [GitHub: /data]
ğŸ“Œ Note: For large datasets, contact the project administrators before uploading.

4ï¸âƒ£ Integrate with AI Models
Use Jupyter Notebooks on EBRAINS to preprocess and analyze data.
Run data harmonization scripts to standardize formats.
Train AI models with newly integrated patient cohorts.
